It’s 100 degrees outside but in this home, it’s fall 🍁☕️ Fun fact: my first job at 16 was working in a bakery and these were my favorite thing to make (and eat) 😋

CINNAMON DONUT MINI MUFFINS:

• 1 1/2 c flour
• 1/2 c sugar 
• 1 1/2 tsp baking powder
• 1/8 tsp salt
• 1/2 tsp cinnamon
• 1/4 tsp nutmeg
• 1 tsp vanilla extract
• 1 egg
• 1/2 c milk
• 1/3 c melted butter (cooled)

Topping:
• 1/2 cup sugar
• 2 tsp cinnamon
• 1 stick melted butter

Bake at 350 for 16-18 minutes. Cool on wire rack (doesn’t need to cool all the way, just cool enough to handle). Roll in melted butter, then cinnamon sugar. Enjoy!!!!! 😋🍁

Pack my carry on bag with me ✈️💖 This Sugarberry bag fits PERFECTLY under the seat in front of you and is so easily accessible during your flight. Here is a list of my travel day essentials:
• water bottle + electrolyte packets 💦
• laptop + chargers (portable charger for flights without outlets!) 💻 
• air pods 🎵 
• wallet (keep in the front pocket for easy access)
• lip balm/gloss 😘 
• hair ties/claw clip
• hand sanitizer, wet wipes + tissues 
• gum or chewy candy 🍬
• tums/pain relievers 💊 
• first aid kit (just in case!)
• travel pillow for long flights 💤 

What’s in your travel bag that you can’t live without?
